Etymology 1[edit]

Noun[edit]

pedīculō

  1. dative singular of pedīculus
  2. ablative singular of pedīculus

Etymology 2[edit]

From pēdīculus.

Verb[edit]

pēdīculō (present infinitive pēdīculāre, perfect active pēdīculāvī, supine pēdīculātum); first conjugation

  1. I free from lice; delouse.
